cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.CC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses a mathematical formulation of dynamics and intensionality of computation, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper presents a new game semantics of a programming language, which captures intensionality of computation and models dynamics of computation. 
- cs.TL (Temporal Logic): The paper deals with the dynamics of computation, which can be seen as a temporal process. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the operational aspects of computation, which can be related to computational complexity. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper presents a mathematical foundation of operational aspects of computation, which can be relevant to software engineering.
